init_text: Your entire life, you've been told you're deathly allergic to bees. You've always had people protecting you from them, be it your mother or a hired hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I know it can be life-threatening to some people, but as anaphylactic shock is a bit out of my comfort zone.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "But I have no idea how to be a queen," I said.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The bee then told me that he had a wife and children at home and that soon, they would all starve because their crops have failed.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So I walked the bee and his family out to their farm and we started watering their crops.

actions.name: text-insert
